 Mr John Oupa Hobe (41) was a local from Mathaileng, Mhluzi. Hobe was fatally shot in the head after the armed robbers brazenly opened fire in a full-blown armed assault.
After Mr Hobe was struck, medics at the scene fought to keep him alive and stabilise him before he was rushed to hospital. Also read: WATCH: Armed robbers open fire on unsuspecting civilians According to other media houses, the national police spokesperson, Brenda Muridili, announced that Mr Hobe was a petrol attendant under the filling station’s employment.
It was later confirmed to be untrue and Mr Hobe was a patron who was busy refueling his vehicle at the time of the attack. The deceased was one of three civilians who was struck by stray bullets in the armed assault.
A mother from Aerorand and her seven year-old daughter were both wounded in the leg. Also read: Update: Man shot in Midwater heist succumbs to his wounds The Middelburg SAPS have confirmed that a case of murder, as well as two attempted murders, have been opened and that the Hawks are currently leading the investigation.
